[For a map of Inner Mongolia, see
<http://www.spiritone.com/~brucem/imar_map.jpg>.
The apparent delay in internationally notifying the avian influenza
outbreak in Inner Mongolia illuminates the need for improved
transparency. China's transparency on human and animal-health issues
seems to have been steadily improving since the SARS outbreak, as
reflected by this released news about the (when?) outbreak; further
improvement is expected. The Chinese seem to be perfectly aware of
the expectations; according to an article "Watchful eye on epidemics
during olympiad," published today (Wed 19 Oct 2005) by the official
Xinhuanet, China's public health authorities will report daily
occurrences of epidemics during the Beijing Olympiad to be held in
August 2008. See
<http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2005-10/18/content_3643765.htm>. - Mod.AS]
